An Iyaganku Chief Magistrates’ Court sitting in Ibadan on Friday, ordered that a security guard, Tirimisiyu Oladeji, 60, who allegedly raped a 13-year-old girl be remanded in prison custody pending legal advice. Chief Magistrate O.O. Ogunkammi did not take the plea of Oladeji, who resides in Oke – Sapati area of Ibadan, NAN reports. Ogunkammi ordered that Oladeji be remanded in Agodi prison pending the outcome of legal advice from the office of the Oyo State Department of Public Prosecution. The magistrate adjourned the matter until Sept.27, for mention. The Prosecution Counsel, Insp. Sikiru Opaleye told the court that Oladeji in June, at Jericho area of Ibadan, raped the girl. He said the offence contravened provisions of Section 357 and is punishable under Section 358 of the Criminal Code Cap 38, Vol.II, Laws of Oyo State 2000. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.